            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Product 1 -->
    <section class="section" id="canon-r100">
      <div class="product-review-card">
        <div class="product-review-header">
          <div class="product-image-container">
            <span class="badge-best">üí∞ Cheapest Option</span>
            <picture>
  <source srcset="/assets/images/guides/canon-r100.webp" type="image/webp">
  <img src="/assets/images/guides/canon-r100.webp" alt="Canon EOS R100" loading="lazy">
</picture>
          </div>
          <div class="product-info">
            <h3 class="product-title">Canon EOS R100</h3>
            <p>
              This is currently the cheapest mirrorless camera on the market that includes a viewfinder. It strips away
              fancy features like touch screens and flip-out displays to focus purely on image quality.
            </p>
            <p>
              It uses the same 24MP sensor found in much more expensive Canon cameras, meaning your photos will look
              identical to those from a $1,000 body. Ideally suited for students who strictly want to learn photography.
            </p>

            <div class="specs-list">
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Sensor</span>
                <span class="spec-value">24MP APS-C</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Screen</span>
                <span class="spec-value">Fixed (Non-Touch)</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">AF</span>
                <span class="spec-value">Eye Detection</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Weight</span>
                <span class="spec-value">356g</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <a href="#" class="btn-buy" data-product="canon-r100" rel="sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
              Check Price on Amazon &rarr;
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros">
            <h4>Pros</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Incredible image quality for the price</li>
              <li>Compact and lightweight</li>
              <li>Includes an electronic viewfinder (EVF)</li>
              <li>Great Canon colors</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="cons">
            <h4>Cons</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Screen is fixed and not a touchscreen</li>
              <li>4K video has a heavy crop & bad autofocus</li>
              <li>Uses older, slower technology</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Product 2 -->
    <section class="section" id="sony-zv-e10">
      <div class="product-review-card">
        <div class="product-review-header">
          <div class="product-image-container">
            <span class="badge-best">üèÜ Value King</span>
            <!-- Reusing ZV-E10 II image but referencing Gen 1 as budget option concept, or simply using same style image -->
            <picture>
  <source srcset="/assets/images/guides/sony-zv-e10-ii.webp" type="image/webp">
  <img src="/assets/images/guides/sony-zv-e10-ii.webp" alt="Sony ZV-E10" loading="lazy">
</picture>
          </div>
          <div class="product-info">
            <h3 class="product-title">Sony ZV-E10</h3>
            <p>
              Even with a successor out, the original ZV-E10 remains the king of value. You get 4K video, a fully
              articulating screen, a headphone jack, and microphone input‚Äîfeatures usually reserved for $1,000+ cameras.
            </p>
            <p>
              The autofocus is still miles ahead of competitors in this price bracket. It tracks eyes and faces
              reliably, making it the perfect budget hybrid for YouTubers who also take photos.
            </p>

            <div class="specs-list">
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Sensor</span>
                <span class="spec-value">24MP APS-C</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Video</span>
                <span class="spec-value">4K30 (Uncropped)</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Lens</span>
                <span class="spec-value">Sony E-Mount</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Mic</span>
                <span class="spec-value">3-Capsule (Good)</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <a href="#" class="btn-buy" data-product="sony-zv-e10" rel="sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
              Check Price on Amazon &rarr;
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros">
            <h4>Pros</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Access to affordable Sigma/Tamron lenses</li>
              <li>Fully flip-out screen for selfies/vlogging</li>
              <li>Reliable face/eye autofocus</li>
              <li>Headphone and Mic ports included</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="cons">
            <h4>Cons</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>No viewfinder (screen only)</li>
              <li>Rolling shutter (jello effect) in 4K</li>
              <li>Menus are the older, confusing style</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Product 3 -->
    <section class="section" id="lumix-g100d">
      <div class="product-review-card">
        <div class="product-review-header">
          <div class="product-image-container">
            <span class="badge-best">üì∏ Tiny Hybrid</span>
            <picture>
  <source srcset="/assets/images/guides/panasonic-g100d.webp" type="image/webp">
  <img src="/assets/images/guides/panasonic-g100d.webp" alt="Panasonic Lumix G100D" loading="lazy">
</picture>
          </div>
          <div class="product-info">
            <h3 class="product-title">Panasonic Lumix G100D</h3>
            <p>
              The G100D is a tiny camera with a big heart. It uses the smaller Micro Four Thirds sensor, which allows
              the camera and lenses to be incredibly portable. It has a beautiful, bright electronic
              viewfinder‚Äîsomething the Sony ZV-E10 lacks.
            </p>
            <p>
              It features Nokia OZO audio tracking which focuses audio on whoever is speaking. It's a fantastic, often
              overlooked option for travel vlogging on a shoestring budget.
            </p>

            <div class="specs-list">
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Sensor</span>
                <span class="spec-value">20MP M4/3</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Viewfinder</span>
                <span class="spec-value">High Res OLED</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Audio</span>
                <span class="spec-value">Nokia OZO</span>
              </div>
              <div class="spec-item">
                <span class="spec-label">Charge</span>
                <span class="spec-value">USB-C</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <a href="#" class="btn-buy" data-product="panasonic-g100d" rel="sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
              Check Price on Amazon &rarr;
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros">
            <h4>Pros</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Excellent viewfinder for bright days</li>
              <li>Huge selection of cheap used lenses</li>
              <li>Advanced audio features built-in</li>
              <li>USB-C charging (updated model)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="cons">
            <h4>Cons</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Heavy crop in 4K video</li>
              <li>Autofocus pulses (hunting) in video</li>
              <li>Smaller sensor than APS-C rivals</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Budget Buying Advice</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Buy Used to Save 30%</h3>
          <p>Cameras are durable. Buying a used "Like New" body from reputable dealers like MPB or KEH is the smartest
            way to stretch your budget.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Kit Lens is Fine</h3>
          <p>Don't stress about expensive lenses yet. The 18-50mm (or similar) kit lens that comes with these cameras is
            perfect for learning the basics.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

  
    <!-- Author Box -->
    <section class="section author-box">
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; align-items: flex-start;">
        <img src="/assets/images/team-avatar.webp" alt="cameraupick Editorial Team" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; border-radius: 50%; object-fit: contain; background: white; border: 2px solid var(--accent); padding: 4px;">
        <div>
          <h4 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0;">Written by cameraupick Editorial Team</h4>
          <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px;">
            Our team of professional photographers and videographers has 10+ years of experience testing cameras. 
            We buy our own gear and provide honest, unbiased reviews.
          </p>
          <a href="/about" style="font-size: 14px; margin-top: 8px; display: inline-block;">Learn more about our testing process ‚Üí</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  
